Hi,<BR>
<BR>
I have torque 2.1.6 installed under /usr from a debian package. I am trying to configure openmpi 1.1.4 using --wth-tm. <BR>
<BR>
The file tm.h is installed under /usr/include/torque. If I use --with-tm=/usr then tm.h is not found. The only way I can get this to work is if I copy tm.h to /usr/include. <BR>
<BR>
Is there a better way to do this? Is the torque debian package wrong putting tm.h inside /usr/include/torque?<BR>
<BR>
Regards,<BR>
Simeon<BR>
